 ✅ 1) Introduction to JavaScript

JavaScript is a single-threaded, interpreted, dynamically typed language used to create interactive web applications.
It is synchronous by default but can handle asynchronous operations using callbacks, promises, and async/await.

Key Points :

What is Synchronous?
Synchronous code runs line by line.
Each task waits for the previous one to finish.

What is Asynchronous?
Asynchronous code does NOT block execution.
Long-running tasks run in the background, and JS continues.

What is Single-Threaded?
JavaScript has only ONE call stack.
It can execute only one task at a time

Uses:

DOM manipulation
Event handling
API calls

