✅ 5) What are Functions? Arrow Functions?

Functions are reusable blocks of code.
Arrow functions provide short syntax and lexical this.

function add(a, b) {
&nbsp; return a + b;
}

const multiply = (a, b) => a * b;
console.log(add(2,3));
console.log(multiply(2,3));

Why Use Arrow Functions?
Short \& Clean Syntax
2.Arrow functions do not have their own this. Arrow functions inherit this from their parent scope.

