✅ 7) Callbacks ⭐⭐

What is a Callback?
A callback is a function passed as an argument to another function and executed later, usually after some task is completed.

👉 Used mainly in asynchronous operations.

Simple Example:
function greet(name, callback) {
&nbsp; console.log("Hello " + name);
&nbsp; callback();
}

function sayBye() {
&nbsp; console.log("Goodbye");
}

greet("Raj", sayBye);

Callback Hell (🔥 VERY IMPORTANT)
When callbacks are nested inside callbacks, making code:
•	Hard to read
•	Hard to debug
•	Hard to maintain

📌 Also called Pyramid of Doom

Why Callback Hell is a Problem?
❌ Difficult to read
❌ Difficult to debug
❌ Error handling becomes complex
❌ Code grows horizontally

How to Avoid Callback Hell? (Interview Point)
•	Promises
•	async / await

