✅ 8) Promises ⭐⭐⭐

>> What is a Promise?
A Promise represents a value that will be available now, later, or never.
A Promise has 3 states:
•	Pending
•	Fulfilled
•	Rejected



>> What is async/await?
async/await is syntactic sugar over promises.
It makes asynchronous code look synchronous and easier to read.

Key Difference (Core Concept)
👉 Both use Promises internally
👉 async/await is NOT a replacement, it is a cleaner way to use promises

Promises handle asynchronous operations using .then() and .catch(), while async/await is a cleaner syntax built 
on top of promises that allows writing asynchronous code in a synchronous style with better readability and error handling.

