✅ 10) Call Stack ⭐⭐

What is Call Stack?
The Call Stack is a data structure that keeps track of function calls in JavaScript.
👉 JavaScript executes code one function at a time using the call stack.
🧠 Rule
•	LIFO (Last In, First Out)

Web APIs (Browser Feature)
When JavaScript sees asynchronous code, it sends it to Web APIs:
•	setTimeout
•	setInterval
•	DOM events
•	fetch

👉 JS does not wait for them.

Callback Queue & Microtask Queue
🔹 Callback Queue
•	Stores callbacks from:
o	setTimeout
o	setInterval
o	DOM events

🔹 Microtask Queue (Higher Priority)
•	Stores callbacks from:
o	Promise.then
o	catch
o	finally
o	async/await

📌 Microtask Queue executes BEFORE Callback Queue

What is Event Loop?
The Event Loop continuously checks:

1\.	Is Call Stack empty?
2\.	If yes:
o	Execute Microtask Queue
o	Then execute Callback Queue
👉 This is how JS handles asynchronous code despite being single-threaded.

